        <section eId="sec_383_42">
          <num>383-42</num>
          <heading>Representation</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§383-42  Representation.
The department
of labor and industrial relations shall be a party and be entitled to notice in
any proceeding involving a claim for benefits before the referee.  In any
proceeding for judicial review pursuant to section 383-41, the department may
be represented by any qualified attorney employed by the department and
designated by it for that purpose, or at the department's request by the
attorney general. [L 1939, c 219, §6(h); am L 1941, c 304, §1, pt of subs 18;
RL 1945, §4243; RL 1955, §93-41; am L Sp 1959 2d, c 1, §27; HRS §383-42]
